perl-SDL
-------------------------------------------
SDL_perl is a package of perl modules that provides both functional and
object orient interfaces to the Simple DirectMedia Layer for Perl 5. 
This package does take some liberties with the SDL API, and attempts to 
adhere to the spirit of both the SDL and Perl. 

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-1.7.0-61
  libgcc1-4.3.2-2
  libGL1-7.4.4-1
  libGLU1-7.4.4-1
  libSDL1.2_0-1.2.13-10
  libSDL_gfx13-2.0.19-1
  libSDL_image1.2_0-1.2.7-10
  libSDL_mixer1.2_0-1.2.8-10
  libSDL_net1.2_0-1.2.7-10
  libSDL_ttf2.0_0-2.0.9-10
  libsmpeg0.4_0-0.4.4-10
  perl-5.10.0-5

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding devel packages)
  binutils-2.19.51-1
  cygport-0.9.9-1
  gcc4-core-4.3.2-2
  gcc4-g++-4.3.2-2
  make-3.81-2

Canonical homepage:
  http://sdl.perl.org/

Canonical download:
  http://www.cpan.org/authors/id/K/KT/KTHAKORE/

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  unpack perl-SDL-2.2.2.17-X-src.tar.bz2
    if you use setup to install this src package, it will be
	 unpacked under /usr/src automatically
  cd /usr/src
  cygport ./perl-SDL-2.2.2.17-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/perl-SDL-2.2.2.17-X-src.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/perl-SDL-2.2.2.17-X.tar.bz2

-------------------------------------------

